Ur. Rojas 1s
under the Impression that those pictures

S. Adams.
enos.

Black and white photograph depicting Pan American World Airways captain Roger Sherron and officials standing in front of Douglas DC-4 “Clipper Dreadnought” airplane at night for inaugural celebration of international wing at Mexico City Airport, December 1946.b. Typed correspondence from F. S. Adams to R. Sherron regarding enclosure of four photographs.c. Mailing envelope with label, “Compania Mexicana de Aviación.”
